    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is actually intended behavior - due to bad performance of nested `text` nodes in RN, we unfortunately have to be more restrictive and can't allow hierarchic text formatting, meaning that something can be bold and link and the same time, etc.\r\nSo the current logic is to always take the outermost \"wrapping\" modifier, so if some text is formatted as bold/italic/codequote, anything inside (tag, link, other formatting) is not taken into account.",
